        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 4:36PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 436 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 23 miles north of Clayton Lake State Park, or 27 miles
east of Des Moines, and are nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grenville.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 394 and 408.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
